The paper discusses the discrete cosine transform (DCT) and its applications in compression standards, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also focuses on image compression performance, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The use of FPGA technology and hardware architectures indicates a possible fit with multimedia (cs.MM) and computer architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories. Finally, the proposed metric for combining performance and computational complexity measures suggests a potential connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
